The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Bill to check corruption
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bill to check corruption
                            
	Patna, Dec. 30 (PTI): Bihar cabinet today cleared a Bihar Special Court Bill, 2008.        
	The bill is aimed at taking action against government employees for acquiring wealth beyond their known sources of income.         
	Armed with the bills provisions the vigilance sleuths would now on be able to take punitive actions against corrupt government officials and lodge disproportionate asset (DA) case against them.         
	Cabinet and co-ordination secretary, Girish Shanker told reporters after the cabinet meeting that the officials, if found guilty, would be booked under DA case and their properties  moveable and immovable  would be seized and they would be tried by a special court.         
	Shanker said the bill also envisaged constitution of a special court headed by a district judge or additional district judge for speedy trial of DA cases.         
	The cabinet also decided to hand over the closed sugar mills at Sugauli and Lauriya to HPCL.                                                                                                                                                                         
